<p><italic>Social Psychology Quarterly</italic> retracts the article “The Norm-activating Power of Celebrity: The Dynamics of Success and Influence,” by Siegwart Lindenberg, Janneke F. Joly, and Diederik A. Stapel, which appeared in the March 2011 issue (74(1):98–120; DOI: 10.1177/0190272511398208). This retraction stems from the results of an investigation into the work of Diederik A. Stapel (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.commissielevelt.nl/noort-committee/publications-examined/">https://www.commissielevelt.nl/noort-committee/publications-examined/</ext-link>), which finds strong evidence of fraud in the dataset supplied by Stapel. His coauthors had no knowledge of his actions and were not involved in the production of the fraudulent data.</p>
</abstract>
